{"cursor":"2634","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Hymns of the Saints', published in Independence, Missouri by Herald House in\n1981, is the official English language hymnal of the Community of Christ. The\nhymnal contains 501 Christian hymns representing a variety of musical styles.\n\nHarold Neal served as Chairman of the 1981 Hymnal Committee and production of\nthe Hymns of the Saints was coordinated by Peter Judd of the Worship Office and\nRoger Revell of the Music Office. In the preface to the work, the committee\nacknowledges the influence of âchanging theological concepts, the searching eye\nof historical research, shifting modes of expression, and increased sensitivity\nto the sanctity of personhoodâ in the preparation of the hymnal and the\nselection of hymns.\n\nOf the 501 hymns, 209 were not found in [[The Hymnal (Community of Christ)|The\nHymnal]], which was published in 1956. The hymns are organized in four major\nsections: Praise and Thanksgiving (hymns 1â78); Contemplation and Renewal\n(hymns 79â185); Godâs Word for Us (186â368); and Commission and Commitment\n(hymns 369â501).\n\nIn the hymnal, 127 lyrical contributions and 88 musical contributions were made\nby members of the denomination while the remainder are from earlier Latter Day\nSaint and Christian hymnists. Aside from six hymn texts drawn directly from the\npsalms (Hymns 15, 66, 110, 125, 258, and 461), the earliest Christian text is\nattributed to Aurelius Clemens Prudentius, who lived from 348 to 413; he is\ncredited as the original author of the text from which Hymn 220, \"Of the\nFatherâs Love Begotten\", was translated by John Mason Neale and Henry W. Baker.\n\nAmong the most prolific contributors to the texts of the hymns in the book are\n(number of contributions are noted in parentheses) Roy Cheville (13), Geoffrey\nF. Spencer (13), Isaac Watts (12), Charles Wesley (11), Allan Tyree (10), Fred\nKaan (9), Evan A. Fry (9), Naomi Russell (7), and Barbara Howard (6).\nhttp://www.graceland.edu/finearts/music.cfm?durki=4028\n\nHymns of the Saints was cited as a catalyst for inspiration by Community of\nChrist President Stephen M. Veazey in his discussion of Doctrine and Covenants\nSection 163. Veazey, Stephen M., Doctrine and Covenants 163: My Testimony,\nweb page, viewed online January 8, 2008 at http://www.cofchrist.org/D&C163/commentary-\nVeazey.asp\n","linknr":113,"url":"Hymns_of_the_Saints","recorded":1375072562,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Hymns_of_the_Saints&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Hymns_of_the_Saints&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Independence,_Missouri","/wiki/Herald_House","/wiki/English_language","/wiki/Hymnal","/wiki/Community_of_Christ","/wiki/Hymn","/wiki/Preface","/w/index.php?title=The_Hymnal_(Community_of_Christ)&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Latter_Day_Saint","/wiki/Psalms","/wiki/John_Mason_Neale","/wiki/Roy_Cheville","/wiki/Isaac_Watts","/wiki/Charles_Wesley","#cite_note-1","/wiki/President_of_the_Church","/wiki/Stephen_M._Veazey","/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants","#cite_note-2","/w/index.php?title=Hymns_of_the_Saints&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-1","http://www.graceland.edu/finearts/music.cfm?durki=4028","